From: anthropic-punctilio
Subject: [PATCH] Fold U+02BB and U+02BC modifier letter apostrophes in find-in-page

Find-in-page currently folds several Unicode quote characters to their
ASCII equivalents so users can search with straight quotes and match
curly quotes on the page. However, U+02BB MODIFIER LETTER TURNED COMMA
and U+02BC MODIFIER LETTER APOSTROPHE are not included in this folding.

U+02BB is used as a letter in Hawaiian (ʻokina), Tongan, and Samoan.
U+02BC is the Unicode-recommended character for representing the
apostrophe in languages where it functions as a letter (e.g., Kazakh
Latin, several African orthographies). It is also used by typographic
libraries that distinguish the apostrophe from the closing single
quotation mark. When a page uses either character, searching for a
straight apostrophe (') or a curly apostrophe (U+2019) fails to find
the text, which is confusing for users.

This CL adds U+02BB and U+02BC to the existing quote-folding logic so
that they are treated as equivalent to a straight single quote in
find-in-page.

Bug: none
Change-Id: (to be generated by Gerrit)
---
 .../blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities.cc      | 8 +++++++-
 .../renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities_test.cc       | 8 ++++++--
 .../blink/renderer/platform/wtf/text/character_names.h     | 2 ++
 3 files changed, 15 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/text/character_names.h b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/text/character_names.h
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/text/character_names.h
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/text/character_names.h
@@ -51,6 +51,7 @@ const UChar kLatinSmallLetterSharpS = 0x00DF;
 // U+0***
 const UChar kLatinCapitalLetterIWithDotAbove = 0x0130;
 const UChar kLatinSmallLetterDotlessI = 0x0131;
+const UChar kModifierLetterTurnedComma = 0x02BB;
+const UChar kModifierLetterApostrophe = 0x02BC;
 const UChar kLatinSmallLetterDotlessJ = 0x0237;
 const UChar kCombiningAcuteAccent = 0x0301;
 const UChar kCombiningMinusSignBelow = 0x0320;
diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities.cc
@@ -44,6 +44,7 @@ static inline CharType FoldQuoteMarkOrSoftHyphen(CharType c) {
       return '"';
     case uchar::kHebrewPunctuationGeresh:
     case uchar::kLeftSingleQuotationMark:
+    case uchar::kModifierLetterTurnedComma:
+    case uchar::kModifierLetterApostrophe:
     case uchar::kRightSingleQuotationMark:
       return '\'';
     case uchar::kSoftHyphen:
@@ -59,6 +60,8 @@ void FoldQuoteMarksAndSoftHyphens(String& s) {
   s.Replace(uchar::kHebrewPunctuationGeresh, '\'');
   s.Replace(uchar::kHebrewPunctuationGershayim, '"');
   s.Replace(uchar::kLeftDoubleQuotationMark, '"');
   s.Replace(uchar::kLeftSingleQuotationMark, '\'');
+  s.Replace(uchar::kModifierLetterTurnedComma, '\'');
+  s.Replace(uchar::kModifierLetterApostrophe, '\'');
   s.Replace(uchar::kRightDoubleQuotationMark, '"');
   s.Replace(uchar::kRightSingleQuotationMark, '\'');
   // Replace soft hyphen with an ignorable character so that their presence or
diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities_test.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities_test.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities_test.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/text/unicode_utilities_test.cc
@@ -79,13 +79,17 @@ TEST(UnicodeUtilitiesTest, FoldQuoteMarkOrSoftHyphenTest) {
                                      uchar::kRightDoubleQuotationMark,
                                      uchar::kHebrewPunctuationGeresh,
                                      uchar::kLeftSingleQuotationMark,
+                                     uchar::kModifierLetterTurnedComma,
+                                     uchar::kModifierLetterApostrophe,
                                      uchar::kRightSingleQuotationMark,
                                      uchar::kSoftHyphen};

   String string_to_fold{base::span(kCharactersToFold)};
   Vector<UChar> buffer;
   string_to_fold.AppendTo(buffer);

   FoldQuoteMarksAndSoftHyphens(string_to_fold);

-  const String folded_string(base::span_from_cstring("\"\"\"\'\'\'\0"));
+  const String folded_string(base::span_from_cstring("\"\"\"\'\'\'\'\'\0"));
   ASSERT_EQ(std::size(kCharactersToFold), folded_string.length());
   EXPECT_EQ(string_to_fold, folded_string);
